The formula for the calculation of operating cash flow is as follows:

$$\begin{aligned} 
\text{Operating CF} &= \text{(Selling price - Variable cost)} 
\times\text{No. of units applied} \\ 
& \qquad \text{ - Fixed cost} \times(1-\text{Tax rate)} \text{+(Tax rate}\times\text{Depreciation)}\\[15pt]
\end{aligned}
$$

Hence, the formula and the computation will be like this:

$$\begin{aligned} 
\text{Operating CF} &= \ \text{(Selling price - Variable cost)}\times\text{No. of units applied}\\
& \qquad \text{ - Fixed cost}\times(1-\text{Tax rate)} \text{+(Tax rate}\times\text{Depreciation)}\\[15pt]
&=\text{(\$280 - \$185)}\times\text{36,000}\text{ - \$985,000}\\
& \qquad \times(1-\text{0.38)}\text{+(0.38}\times\text{\$1,040,000)}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\bf{\$1,904,900}}
\end{aligned}
$$

Therefore, the operating cash flow for this is amounting to $1,904,900.
